# User Engagement A/B Testing

## Overview
This project simulates an A/B test to analyze user engagement and evaluate which version of a product performs better.

## What This Does
- Splits users into Group A and Group B
- Simulates user behavior (time spent and clicks)
- Compares performance between groups

## Key Metrics
- Average time spent
- Click-through rate

## Insight
Group B shows improved engagement, demonstrating how A/B testing helps guide product decisions.

## Tools Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
